      • DualHashMap

        public DualHashMap()
        Instantiate a basic DualHashMap. This HashMap is designed to keep individual keys and individual values unique.

    • Method Detail

      • put

        public void put(K key,
                V value)
        Adds a key and value to the DualHashMap. If the key is associated with an existing value, that key will be removed and vice versa.
        Specified by:
        put in interface DualMap<K,V>
        Parameters:
        key - The key to be added.
        value - The value to be added and associated with a key.

      • remove

        public void remove(K key,
                   V value)
        Removes the mapping from the key to the value from this dual map if it is present. After dualmap.put(key, value) and dualmap.remove(key, value), then dualmap.get(key) should return null and dualmap.reverseGet(value) should return null.
        Specified by:
        remove in interface DualMap<K,V>
        Parameters:
        key - key whose mapping to value is to be removed
        value - value whose mapping from key is to be removed

      • get

        public V get(K key)
        Returns the value that maps from the specified key, or null if this dual map contains no mapping for the key.
        Specified by:
        get in interface DualMap<K,V>
        Parameters:
        key - the key that maps to the value that should be returned
        Returns:
        the value that maps from the specified key, or null if this dual map contains no mapping for the key

      • reverseGet

        public K reverseGet(V value)
        Returns the key that maps to the specified value, or null if this dual map contains no mapping for the value.
        Specified by:
        reverseGet in interface DualMap<K,V>
        Parameters:
        value - the value that maps from the key that should be returned
        Returns:
        the key that maps to the specified value, or null if this dual map contains no mapping for the value
